Package youtube.classes

package youtube.classes
  • Related Packages
    Package
    Description
    youtube
     
  • Class
    Description
    Channel
    The Channel class represents a channel It stores information about the channel, such as channel ID, followers, uploaded videos and uploaded streams Implements Serializable for object serialization and Subject for observers.
    Observer
    The Observer interface represents an object that can observe changes in a subject.
    Stream
    The Stream class represents a live stream It stores information about the stream, such as stream ID, name, description, start time, number of likes, and number of users Implements Serializable for object serialization and Watchable for watchable items.
    Subject
    The Subject interface represents an object that can be observed by observers.
    User
    The User class represents a user It stores basic information about user ( e.g name, thumbnail, list of streams and videos to watch and informations about current watching content Implements Serializable to support object serialization and Observer for updates.
    Video
    The Video class represents a video It stores basic information about the video (e.g such as video ID, name, description, duration, upload date, number of views, number of likes, and premium status) Implements Serializable for object serialization and Watchable for watchable items.
    Watchable
    The Watchable interface represents a content that can be watched by user It defines methods for obtaining information about the item, such as its current view, general information, version status, duration, and index.
